defs.name: cubic_spline_interpolate
defs.value:
pub fn cubic_spline_interpolate<T>(f32, &[f32], &[T], bool) -> T where
T: InterpolationPrimitive + Clone

attributes.value: / `m0 = out tangent at left keyframe * (t1 - t0)`
/ `m1 = in tangent at right keyframe * (t1 - t0)`
/ - `input`: the input value to the function
/ - `inputs`: list of discrete input values for each keyframe
/ - `outputs`: list of output values to interpolate between, for cubic spline interpolation this
/             should three times the size of `inputs` and defined as
/             `[ in_tangent_0, position_0, out_tangent_0, in_tangent_1, position_1, out_tangent_1, .. ]`
/ - `normalize`: if true, normalize the interpolated value before returning it

/ error around 10^-4, but runs much faster because it does no trigonometry or sqrt calls.
/ Algorithm was created by Jonathan Blow:

/ - `normalize`: if true, normalize the interpolated value before returning it
